wikipedia_page.main: Mary MacLeod Banks (1861 – 22 December 1951) was a folklorist, born Mary MacLeod McConnel in Scotland. She was president of the Folklore Society from 1937 to 1939.

response: **Mary MacLeod Banks (née McConnel; 1861–1951), her daughter, a British-Australian folklorist
One of the McConnels' daughters was the folklorist of the same name, Mary MacLeod Banks (née McConnel).
